<HEADLINE>
<P>
VETERAN'S SEARCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Thanks very much to staff writer Greg Krikorian for his wonderfully written and 
very moving Veterans Day story (Metro, Nov. 12) on Wallace Perry, a World War 
II veteran who journeyed to Belgium on behalf of a woman he barely knew to find 
the grave of her father who had been killed in battle back in 1944, and to lay 
a medal on the grave site. 
</P>
<P>
It really was frustrating to hear that Perry was unable to locate the woman 
upon his return to tell her of his success. That made the follow-up article 
(Nov. 16) all the more satisfying to find out that the woman had indeed been 
found, and that she was thrilled and touched. 
</P>
<P>
RON GRACEN 
</P>
<P>
Van Nuys 
</P>
</TEXT>
