Letter to the Editor 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA112490-0041 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 312513 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
November 24, 1990, Saturday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Sports; Part C; Page 3; Column 1; Sports Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
66 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAGIC, HEARN CHARGED WITH WRONG RESPONSE TO ARREST OF WORTHY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Millionaire James Worthy, whose business is playing basketball with the Lakers, 
is arrested for soliciting a prostitute or prostitutes in Houston, we learn 
after the game. 
</P>
<P>
Chick Hearn wouldn't breathe a word of it. In all events, Hearn bends over 
backward to make us believe the Lakers belong essentially to a church. It's too 
late for these kinds of lies. 
</P>
<P>
ROBERT L. GREENFIELD, Goleta 
</P>
</TEXT>
