<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION FOOTBALL PLAYOFFS; 
</P>
<P>
WHITTIER CHRISTIAN RUNS OVER DESERT, 61-28 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
EDWARDS AIR FORCE BASE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Whittier Christian High School running backs Rex Pritchard and Ron Rector 
pounded out a combined 239 yards and five touchdowns as the unbeaten Heralds 
(11-0) moved into the Southern Section Division IX football semifinals with a 
61-28 drubbing of host Desert Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
The victory set up a rematch next Friday with Olympic League rival Cerritos 
Valley Christian, a 24-7 winner over Bishop. 
</P>
<P>
In the last meeting with the Crusaders (6-5), Whitter won, 33-28. 
</P>
<P>
Pritchard rushed for 98 yards and three touchdowns in 19 carries and Rector had 
141 yards and two scores in 14 carries. Pritchard also ran for three two-point 
conversions. 
</P>
<P>
Overall, the Heralds had 380 yards on the ground against Desert (8-4). 
</P>
<P>
Whitter scored 24 points in the first quarter and led, 40-8, by halftime. 
</P>
