<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
MARTIN'S 25 HELPS RANCHO SANTIAGO WIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sophomore forward Erik Martin scored 25 points to lead Rancho Santiago College 
to a 91-69 victory over Citrus in the first round of the College of the Desert 
men's basketball tournament Friday at Palm Desert. 
</P>
<P>
Sophomore guard Brett Pagett scored 16 points and sophomore forward Corie 
Blount added 10 for Rancho Santiago (4-1), the defending state champions. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
In the Ventura men's basketball tournament: 
</P>
<P>
El Camino 70, Cypress 69 -- Steve King scored 31 points, including a layup with 
four seconds left, to lead El Camino. Cypress (2-3) trailed, 66-61, with one 
minute left when Charles Lockard scored eight consecutive points on a 
three-point basket, two free throws and a another three-point basket to give 
Cypress a 69-68 lead with 27 seconds left. 
</P>
<P>
Lockard had 16 points and five assists and Eric Pauley had 22 points, 10 
rebounds and three blocked shots for El Camino (5-2). Pauley played for the 
first time in three games after twisting his right ankle. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
In the College of the Desert women's basketball tournament: 
</P>
<P>
Saddleback 50, Chaffey 49 -- Shannon Garnos scored on a 15-foot jump shot with 
three seconds left to give Saddleback (4-2) a first-round victory. Garnos had 
17 points and Erin Schimeneck had seven points and 11 rebounds for Saddleback. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
In nonconference women's basketball: 
</P>
<P>
Fullerton 92, Ventura 50 -- Keri Erkenbrack scored 18 points to lead host 
Fullerton (5-0). Nicky Duriqi had 17 points and Vicki Evans and Holy Keeton 
each had 14 points for Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
Golden West 123, Compton 84 -- Bits Sirchia set a Golden West single-game 
record with 23 assists. Jennifer Harvey and Dawn Haag each scored 22 points and 
Sirchia added 12 for Golden West, which opened a 31-5 lead. 
</P>
<P>
Adrienne Hughes and Tracy Wolf scored 16 each for Golden West, the defending 
state champions. 
</P>
