<TEXT>
<P>
Ana Cristina Periera had 24 kills and her sister, Ana Carolina Periera, added 
23 kills as West Texas State defeated Chapman College, 15-10, 15-7, 7-15, 15-7, 
in the NCAA Division II South Central Region women's volleyball championship 
Friday in Canyon, Tex. 
</P>
<P>
Top-ranked West Texas State (35-1) advances to the eight-team championship at a 
site to be determined. 
</P>
<P>
Tara Christensen had eight kills for 14th-ranked Chapman, which closed the 
season at 22-14. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
In the Titan Gatorade women's basketball tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Cal State Fullerton 68, Cal State Northridge 35 -- Senior center Genia Miller 
scored 24 points, had 11 rebounds and blocked eight shots to lead the Titans 
past the Matadores in Titan Gym. 
</P>
<P>
Junior point guard Michelle Hennessey, playing her first game with the Titans, 
set school records with 13 assists and eight steals, breaking previous marks of 
11 assists (by Jeannine Battaglia) and seven steals (by Jill Matyuch) set last 
season. 
</P>
