<HEADLINE>
<P>
WHAT ARE FANS FOR? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I really wonder what was going through Melissa Henry's mind when she wrote her 
letter ("Enough already with the letters from incensed New Kids on the Block 
fans!" Calendar, Nov. 10). 
</P>
<P>
Her letter comes as no surprise in an adult society where no one does much of 
anything except complain about students' falling test scores and other 
shortcomings of today's young people. The letters we write as New Kids fans 
allow us to give back to them in some minute way. In our hearts, we know we 
have done the right thing by defending them. 
</P>
<P>
Everything comes to pass anyway, but for now, let the New Kids fans exercise 
their right to freedom of speech. 
</P>
<P>
MICHELLE PARKINSON 
</P>
<P>
Anaheim 
</P>
</TEXT>
