<P>
Manville Plan Criticized: Owens-Corning Fiberglas Corp., which is both a 
co-defendant and beneficiary in the massive Manville asbestos case, complained 
that a proposed reorganization of the cash poor Manville trust is a "disaster." 
At a hearing in U.S. District Court in Brooklyn, N.Y., Owens attorney Roger 
Podesta asked Judge Jack Weinstein to withhold approval of a key element of the 
restructuring plan for the Manville Personal Injury Settlement Trust. A 
cornerstone of the new plan -- submitted to Weinstein on Monday -- is the 
proposal to set up a single class-action suit that combines about 130,000 
federal and state asbestos cases, and to appoint a lawyer committee to 
represent them. 
