<SECTION>
<P>
Business; Part D; Page 5; Column 1; Financial Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
96 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: REAL ESTATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by John O'Dell, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mortgage Brokers: With more and more people crossing banks and S&amp;Ls off 
their lists when they go shopping for mortgage loans, the state's mortgage 
brokers have come into their own. 
</P>
<P>
The brokers generally don't provide funding; they put borrowers and willing 
lenders together. And mortgage brokers now are responsible for a majority of 
the residential loan originations in the state. 
</P>
<P>
So now they've formed an association -- the California Assn. of Mortgage 
Brokers. One of the founding chapters is in Orange County. 
</P>
<P>
The statewide group is headquartered in San Diego. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
