Photo, . . .and those at the Buena Park Mall, right, turned out for the first 
day of the holiday season, but many were content to browse. Department stores 
are cutting prices, hurting smaller businesses unable to compete. ; Photo, 
Specials weren't inducing some shoppers in Santa Ana's Latino district. ; 
Photo, "People . . . seemed to be holding onto their money," said a store 
manager on 4th Street in Santa Ana. AURELIO JOSE BARRERA / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
